## Performance Considerations

### Code Efficiency

```typescript
// ✅ Efficient
const userIds = users.map((user) => user.id);

// ❌ Inefficient
const userIds = [];
for (let i = 0; i < users.length; i++) {
  userIds.push(users[i].id);
}
```

### Resource Usage

```typescript
// ✅ Proper cleanup
useEffect(() => {
  const subscription = subscribe();
  return () => subscription.unsubscribe();
}, []);

// ❌ Memory leak
useEffect(() => {
  subscribe();
}, []);
```

## Security Best Practices

> 📝 See [Tech Stack Documentation - Security Measures](mdc:.cursor/rules/tech-stack.mdc#security-measures) for complete security guidelines.

### Input Validation

```typescript
// ✅ Proper validation
const userSchema = z.object({
  email: z.string().email(),
  age: z.number().min(13),
});

// ❌ Unsafe
function createUser(data: any) {
  // Implementation
}
```

### Authentication

```typescript
// ✅ Secure
const user = await authenticateAndAuthorize(request);
if (!user.canAccess(resource)) {
  throw new AuthError('Unauthorized');
}

// ❌ Insecure
const user = request.user;
// No authorization check
```

Remember: The goal is to write code that is maintainable, secure, and performs well in production, while minimizing the need for changes during code review.
